# Engineering principles

Before editing, read the project structure and existing code. Don't invent
architecture that conflicts with what is already in the repo.

Make small, focused, reversible changes. Don't rewrite entire features
unless explicitly asked.

After 3 failed attempts on the same bug, stop and change strategy: clear
relevant cache, re-read the error, inspect logs, isolate the failing file,
then try a different approach. Don't keep patching randomly.

After any code change, run `npm run build` (which includes `tsc --noEmit`).
If it fails, fix it before claiming the work is done.

When the work is done, report exactly which files changed, why they
changed, and how to test the result. If uncertain about a filename, route,
data shape, or deployment behavior, search the repo and read the code
before acting.
